<center>
<h1>
The Cookie Technology</h1></center>

<center><img SRC="tbullet.gif" height=19 width=24><b>create cookies with
<font face="Lucida Handwriting"><font color="#009900">JavaScript</font></font></b></center>

<p><b><font color="#000000">&lt;HTML></font></b>
<br><b><font color="#000000">&lt;HEAD>&lt;TITLE>JavaScript Cookie Example&lt;/TITLE>&lt;/HEAD></font></b>
<br><b><font color="#000000">&lt;SCRIPT LANGUAGE="JavaScript"></font></b>
<br><b><font color="#000000">document.cookie="username=WSB; path=/; expires=Mon,
01-May-2001 00:00:00 GMT";</font></b>
<br><b><font color="#000000">&lt;/SCRIPT></font></b>
<br><b><font color="#000000">&lt;BODY>I just sent you a cookie!&lt;/BODY></font></b>
<br><b><font color="#000000">&lt;/HTML></font></b>
<br>&nbsp;
<p><b><u><font color="#000000">Notes:</font></u></b>
<ul>
<li>
<b><font color="#000000">Cookies are handled via the built-in document.cookie
object.</font></b></li>

<li>
<b><font color="#000000">Bill Dortch at hIdaho Design has a comprehensive
set of functions for cookie management.&nbsp; All of his functions can
be found at &lt;http://www.hidaho.com/cookies/cookie.txt></font></b></li>
</ul>

